      "creation_date" : 1509124560,
      "post_id" : 218761,
      "comment_id" : 80908039,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The struggle I have with marking everything final by default is that it assumes a developer who didn&#39;t take the effort to make a class suitable for extension is somehow going to spend the time making sure it implements a well-designed interface to facilitate testing. Either the dev is lazy, in which case there is no interface and it&#39;s marked final, or the dev is details-oriented in which case the class supports extension and does not need to be <code>final</code>."
