    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1411364765,
    "last_edit_date" : 1411364765,
    "creation_date" : 1224515527,
    "answer_id" : 218769,
    "question_id" : 218744,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Inheritance is like a chainsaw - very powerful, but awful in the wrong hands. Either you design a class to be inherited from (which can limit flexibility and take a lot longer) or you should prohibit it.</p>\n\n<p>See Effective Java 2nd edition items 16 and 17, or my blog post <a href=\"http://codeblog.jonskeet.uk/2006/03/04/inheritancetax.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">\"Inheritance Tax\"</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
