    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1224524131,
    "creation_date" : 1224524131,
    "answer_id" : 219253,
    "question_id" : 218744,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>If you mark classes and methods as final, you may notice a small performance gain, since the runtime doesn't have to look up the right class method to invoke for a given object. Non-final methods are marked as virtual so that they can be properly extended if needed, final methods can be directly linked or compiled inline in the class.</p>\n"
  }, {
